desc:
Headers for HTTP requests and responses.

In some situations, headers are immutable:

  • HttpRequest and HttpClientResponse always have immutable headers.

  • HttpResponse and HttpClientRequest have immutable headers from the moment the body is written to.

In these situations, the mutating methods throw exceptions.

For all operations on HTTP headers the header name is case-insensitive.

To set the value of a header use the set() method:

request.headers.set(HttpHeaders.cacheControlHeader,
                    'max-age=3600, must-revalidate');

To retrieve the value of a header use the value() method:

print(request.headers.value(HttpHeaders.userAgentHeader));

An HttpHeaders object holds a list of values for each name as the standard allows. In most cases a name holds only a single value, The most common mode of operation is to use set() for setting a value, and value() for retrieving a value.
name: dart:io.HttpHeaders

methods.desc: Adds a header value. The header named name will have the value value added to its list of values. Some headers are single valued, and for these adding a value will replace the previous value. If the value is of type DateTime a HTTP date format will be applied. If the value is a List each element of the list will be added separately. For all other types the default toString method will be used.
methods.example:
Implementation

void add(String name, Object value);
methods.name: add

methods.desc: Remove all headers. Some headers have system supplied values and for these the system supplied values will still be added to the collection of values for the header.
methods.name: clear

methods.desc: Enumerates the headers, applying the function f to each header. The header name passed in name will be all lower case.
methods.example:
Implementation

void forEach(void f(String name, List<String> values));
methods.name: forEach

methods.desc: Disables folding for the header named name when sending the HTTP header. By default, multiple header values are folded into a single header line by separating the values with commas. The 'set-cookie' header has folding disabled by default.
methods.name: noFolding

methods.desc: Removes a specific value for a header name. Some headers have system supplied values and for these the system supplied values will still be added to the collection of values for the header.
methods.example:
Implementation

void remove(String name, Object value);
methods.name: remove

methods.desc: Removes all values for the specified header name. Some headers have system supplied values and for these the system supplied values will still be added to the collection of values for the header.
methods.name: removeAll

methods.desc: Sets a header. The header named name will have all its values cleared before the value value is added as its value.
methods.example:
Implementation

void set(String name, Object value);
methods.name: set

methods.desc: Convenience method for the value for a single valued header. If there is no header with the provided name, null will be returned. If the header has more than one value an exception is thrown.
methods.name: value

props.desc: Gets and sets the chunked transfer encoding header value.
props.name: chunkedTransferEncoding

props.desc: Gets and sets the content length header value.
props.name: contentLength

props.desc: Gets and sets the content type. Note that the content type in the header will only be updated if this field is set directly. Mutating the returned current value will have no effect.
props.name: contentType

props.desc: Gets and sets the date. The value of this property will reflect the 'date' header.
props.name: date

props.desc: Gets and sets the host part of the 'host' header for the connection.
